name: 2018/10/10 Dinner
description: This 2018/10/10 Dinner is perfect for those seeking a high-protein, high-fiber lifestyle. Engage in a delightful culinary experience with this healthified recipe, designed to keep you on track with your healthy diet goals while tantalizing your taste buds with its array of flavors.
recipeIngredient: 0.25  tsp ground (2.3 g), Black Pepper - Ground

recipeInstructions.text: Prep your ingredients: Dice the carrots, eggplant, sweet potato, and zucchini into bite-sized pieces. Grate the sharp cheddar cheese.
recipeInstructions.name: Step 1

recipeInstructions.text: Season the sirloin with salt and ground black pepper to taste.
recipeInstructions.name: Step 2

recipeInstructions.text: In a large skillet, melt the butter over medium heat. Add the seasoned sirloin and cook for about 8 minutes on each side for medium-rare, or until desired doneness. Remove the sirloin from the skillet and set aside.
recipeInstructions.name: Step 3

recipeInstructions.text: Cook the diced vegetables until they're tender and lightly browned, about 10 minutes.
recipeInstructions.name: Step 4

recipeInstructions.text: Slice the cooked sirloin into thin strips and return it to the skillet with the vegetables. Stir to combine.
recipeInstructions.name: Step 5

recipeInstructions.text: Sprinkle the grated sharp cheddar cheese over the sirloin and vegetable mix. Cover the skillet and let the cheese melt for about 2 minutes.
recipeInstructions.name: Step 6

recipeInstructions.text: Serve the dish warm, garnished with a pinch of black pepper or fresh herbs if desired.
recipeInstructions.name: Step 7
